[1] UK (Rhyl, Wales)
Date: Thu 4 Jul 2019 21:16 BST
Source: Wales Online [abridged, edited]
https://www.walesonline.co.uk/news/health/measles-symptoms-infectious-rhyl-health-16531810


Several cases of measles have been linked to a cinema, McDonald's restaurant, and a hospital A&E department, it has been revealed.

Public Health Wales has confirmed that a "cluster" of cases of measles has been reported in particular areas of Rhyl, Denbighshire.

A spokeswoman said there are currently 3 confirmed cases of the infection and 2 related suspected cases.

It is understood that these people spent time in public while they were contagious, which means the measles may have spread.

Public Health Wales (PHW) is warning people to be vigilant if they were in any of the [places listed at the source URL above].

[Byline: Mark Smith]

