[4] Europe travel
Date: Mon 1 Jul 2019 17:01 BST
Source: Gloucestershire Live [abridged, edited]
https://www.gloucestershirelive.co.uk/news/regional-news/fears-over-measles-mumps-rubella-3040508


Holidaymakers planning a trip to Europe this summer [2019] are urged to make sure they are up-to-date on their MMR [measles, mumps, rubella] vaccinations says Public Health England.

Public Health England South West wants to make sure that anyone wanting a break in Europe is up-to-date with MMR vaccination.

It comes as campaigning by anti-vaxxers has led to a rise in cases of measles in the UK as well as across Europe in recent years.

There were more than 230 confirmed cases of measles in the UK in the 1st 3 months of this year [2019] alone.

The disease is still endemic in many countries around the world including Europe, with France, Lithuania, Poland, Romania, Bulgaria, and Germany among the countries reporting the highest case counts according to the European Centres for Disease Control and Prevention (ECDC)

The number of cases confirmed in England has been rising since 2018, with many linked to importations from Europe, Public Health England said.

[Byline: Ed Stilliard]

