[5] Canada (Laval, Quebec)
Date: Sun 30 Jun 2019
Source: Yahoo News, CBC (Canadian Broadcasting Corporation) News [abridged, edited]
https://ca.news.yahoo.com/quebec-health-officials-warn-another-211906092.html


Provincial health authorities have declared a 2nd case of measles in recent days in Laval [Quebec] and expanded a list of locations in the city at which people may have been exposed to the virus in late June [2019].

Health authorities say 2 people infected with the virus travelled on several Societe de transport de Laval (STL) buses and visited a gym and a number of commercial areas on Wed 26 Jun and Sat 29 Jun 2019 [listed at the source URL above]. Those people are believed to have been contagious at the time.

A previous measles warning in the area was issued less than a month ago.

