[9] Australia (Sydney, New South Wales) ex SE Asia; (Brisbane, Queensland) ex overseas
Date: Tue 9 Jul 2019 10:43 AM AEST
Source: The Weekly Times, Associated Press (AP) report [abridged, edited]
https://www.weeklytimesnow.com.au/news/national/new-measles-case-in-sydney-after-young-man-developed-symptoms-following-a-trip-to-south-east-asia/news-story/55172959f4ec3f654a18fa29131ff1f7


A young Sydney man who recently returned from travelling around South East Asia has been diagnosed with measles and spent over a week visiting parts of the city while infectious.

NSW [New South Wales] Health issued an alert late this afternoon [9 Jul 2019] as the man, who was vaccinated as a child, had spent time in Hornsby, Lane Cove, Lindfield, the Sydney CBD, Newtown and Erskineville between 30 Jun and 8 Jul 2019 and used public transport [see source URL above for locations.]

Earlier today [9 Jul 2019], another case of measles was reported in Brisbane [Queensland] after a child developed symptoms following an overseas holiday.

The latest case is the 4th in the Metro North area this year [2019], the Brisbane Times reports. The last reported case involved a West Moreton woman who had travelled interstate, according to Queensland Health.

The alert follows a warning sent out by health authorities over the weekend in NSW after a man with measles spent 4 days in Sydney while on holiday from Queensland's Gold Coast.

The man, aged in his 40s, was infectious while travelling [see source URL above for locations].

More than 40 people have been diagnosed with measles in NSW since Christmas [2018]. Despite the high number of people being diagnosed with measles, a recent report has shown vaccination rates in NSW are at their highest levels, with more than 95 per cent of 5-year-olds vaccinated.

